result.execSummary:
Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Restitution hearing on August 13, 2019 at 02:00 pm.

11:04 a.m.  Defendant present in court with Atty Vicki Jobling.  Andrew Christenson for the State of Wisconsin.  Statement by Atty Jobling - will proceed to plea & sentencing.  Atty Jobling recites agreement - in 2016CF92 defendant will enter a NO CONTEST Alford plea to an amended count of 2nd Degree Recklessly Endangering Safety in violation of 941.30(2) with probation and counts 2 & 3 and the balance of the cases will be dismissed and read-in.  DA concurs.  Defendant concurs.  Statement by DA - also a request for restitution on 2016CM136 for $1,028.00.  Statement by Atty Jobling - defendant concurs to the damage but not the amount.  DA confirms compliance with victim witness rights.

Court goes over plea questionnaire with the defendant.  Court goes over constitutional rights with the defendant - defendant waives these rights.  Court goes over the elements of each offense.  Court instructs defendant of the maximum penalty.  Court instructs defendant regarding deportation.  (If felony) Court instructs regarding felony prohibitions.

Defendant enters a plea of NO CONTEST Alford Plea.  Court finds the plea is made freely, voluntarily, intelligently and understandingly.  Court finds there is a factual basis to support the plea.  Court finds the defendant guilty on the amended count 1 in 2016CF92 and orders counts 2 & 3 be dismissed and read-in.  Court orders 2016CM136, 2016CM241 and 2017CF159 be dismissed and read-in.  Court orders the judgment of conviction be entered here today.  Sentencing statement by DA.  Sentencing statement by Atty Jobling.  Statement by the defendant.

Court sentences the defendant to:

2016CF92

-SWD, and places the defendant on probation for 5 years.

CONDITIONS:

-Court costs.  To be paid to the Clerk of Courts office.  Monies are to be paid during the term of probation.  Failure to pay may result in the suspension of your driver's license, tax intercept, a civil judgment being entered against you, a warrant being issued for your arrest for contempt and/or the debt being turned over to a collection agency.
-Defendant is to submit a DNA Sample.
-1 year county jail.  Sentence is to commence within 60 days.  Court grants huber, out-of-county service and out-of-county travel.
-AODA and any follow-up.  If already done, Court leaves it up to the agent.

Restitution - to be determined at a restitution hearing.

Court will set for Restitution Hearing and notify the parties.

Court grants the defendant 6 days of sentence credit if revoked.

Court adjourned at 11:36 a.m.
